Fire on Sunday gutted five offices of Freedom Radio in Kaduna State. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the offices affected included engineering room, office of the Head of Marketing, conference hall, security office, and drivers’ room. Abubakar Usman, the station’s Head of Operations, who confirmed the incident said that the fire, which started around 2:30 am., was put out around 3:30 am. by the personnel of Kaduna State Fire Service. Usman, further stated that there was no loss of life or injury. According to him, the main cause of the fire incident had yet to be ascertained. “The fire consumed five offices; we had to go off-air immediately, but we later resumed around 10:45 am., and God willing, we will continue with our transmission,” he said.